For the first time in this election, RealClearPolitics has put Obama's electoral college total over the 270 necessary to win the presidency, that's not including forcing the distribution of toss-up states. That change came after new polling in Virginia showing Obama with a comfortable lead. Additionaly, U.S. Presidential Poll of Polls: 49.1-43.5% Obama. Source: www.TrulyNewsworthy.com & http://www.realclearpolitics.com.
